Let $r$ be the radius of the red circle.  We see that $\angle AOF = 60^\circ,$ so by the Law of Cosines on triangle $AOF,$
\[AF^2 = AO^2 - AO \cdot OF + OF^2,\]so
\[(1 + r)^2 = \frac{4}{3} - \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3} \cdot (r + s) + (r + s)^2.\]We can isolate $r$ to get
\[r = \frac{3s^2 \sqrt{3} - 6s + \sqrt{3}}{6 + 6 \sqrt{3} - 6s \sqrt{3}} = \frac{3 (\frac{2 \sqrt{3} - 3}{3})^2 \sqrt{3} - 6 \cdot \frac{2 \sqrt{3} - 3}{3} + \sqrt{3}}{6 + 6 \sqrt{3} - 6 \cdot \frac{2 \sqrt{3} - 3}{3} \sqrt{3}} = \frac{9 - 4 \sqrt{3}}{33}.\]The final answer is then $9 + 4 + 3 + 33 = \boxed{49}.$

