\[x^2 + y_1^2 = x^2 + y_2^2 = 4.\]Then $y_1^2 = y_2^2,$ so $y_1 = \pm y_2.$

Furthermore, since $AB = BC = 2$ and $\angle ABC = 90^\circ,$ $AC = 2 \sqrt{2}.$  Hence,
